(OVERVIEW) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(This guide helps operators and maintenance leads respond to fictional carton jams on the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(PKG-605 packaging line. It covers safe stop, jam classification, diverter checks, sensor) Tj
0 -14 Td
(disagreement, and restart validation after a cleared event.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(COMMON SYMPTOMS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Cartons stop at the merge, diverter, or taper entry while upstream zones continue feeding.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- A jam clears physically, but the HMI still shows a blocked zone or latched sensor state.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- One jammed carton causes repeated short stops in the same zone across the shift.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Jam occurs only with taller cartons or mixed-SKU runs near the taper.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(LIKELY CAUSES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Guide rail width set too narrow for the active carton family.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Diverter actuator slow to return or sticking under load.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Photo-eye blocked by label flap, tape tail, or reflective packaging.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Residual carton debris or a bowed carton causing repeat contact at one transfer point.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(DIAGNOSTIC WORKFLOW) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Use the line stop for the affected zone, then confirm upstream release behavior so) Tj
0 -14 Td
(additional cartons are not pushed into the jam point.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Classify the event as simple obstruction, repeat obstruction in the same zone, or control-) Tj
0 -14 Td
(state mismatch where sensors disagree with physical conditions.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Inspect guide rails, diverter movement, belt transition points, and sensor faces before) Tj
0 -14 Td
(resetting the HMI fault.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If the fault persists after the obstruction is removed, compare sensor state on the HMI with) Tj
0 -14 Td
(the physical beam path and manual actuator position.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Check whether the affected carton family matches the setup recipe currently loaded on the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(line.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(RECOVERY ACTIONS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Remove damaged cartons, clean debris, and adjust guide rails only to the approved recipe) Tj
ET
